value.0: The Brogendenstein Dwarves are a stout and hardy folk.
This armor was made from the skin of a bear, enchanted to rival the power and magnificence of the beast. It sports thick fur padding that offers an adequate defense.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this type grant protection equivalent to studded leather or hide.
The Brogendenstein Dwarves have raised their standard of living again.
This is a fine suit of heavy armour bearing the signature of Thargrim from Kakar Runedar.

Value.value: If ya' don't mind I got a lot o' work here.
*Gives you a quick nod before returning to loading up the pack mule.*

value.0: The Hearthguard proudly wear the uniform of Barak Runedar. This one wears an officer's sigil and looks angry.

Value.value: Oi! Ye goin out into tha wilds here? Good. Ye can take a detour.
We got orcs roamin about, causin all kinds o trouble. They attack our gates an our trade wagons up ta Setersborg.
Go take 'em out and bring us back proof o ye deeds an we'll give ye a big ol' sack o coin.
Ugh. Ye get that off their leader? Ruddy smells like it. Ye keep 'em. Take this coin, too. Thank ye fer ye help.
Hail! Go check with tha Raider Captain by tha other gate. He's usually got some more work for adventurer types.
Feck, ye can't find it? Go out into the wilds just over yonder and bear right when ye reach our watchtower. Ye'll see a forest. They be holed up in the middle o that.

value.0: The Runedar Raiders are the famed scouts of Barak Runedar. This one appears to be an officer and paces around as he waits for adventurers to come along.
Developed to protect patroling rangers against a wide variety of foes, this armor is available only to the esteemed defenders of nature.

Value.value: Lost Relics of the Dwarven Kingdom
*looks up from his pacing* Hail. Ye want ta earn a bit o coin? I got a task for ye if so.
We had some old relics go missin recently. Me Raiders tracked the thieves into tha mountains, but we were nay able to retrieve everythin.

Head up there and look for the hole those feckin frost giants live in. They prob'ly gave some o those relics to they chieftain. Get one back for us and ye'll be rewarded. Council has set aside a stockpile jus for this.
That's one! Thank ye. Give that over ta me and I'll give you this piece. *he passes over a large chunk of pink crystal*
Hail there. Thank ye again fer ye help. Council appreciates it and so do me boys. One less relic to worry about bein missin.

Havin trouble navigatin the mountain? Aye, can be easy ta get lost. I'm sure ye'll find it. Just don't go inta the Wastes or the Forest. Ye reach the peak, ye gone too far. Those're fire giants up there.

All laws must be obeyed at all times while on Dwarven lands. Failure to obey Dwarven law and citizens' orders is punishable by, including and up to: removal from Dwarven lands, imprisonment, banishment, and in the most serious and grievous of cases, death. If you feel you have been wronged, contact the Barak Runedar Council with your complaints. Under no circumstances will visitors argue with citizens.


- Visitors will immediately respect dwarven culture and tradition, as well as the orders of citizens without argument.

- Hoods, cowls, helms, and masks that obscure your face and identity must be removed within the Port and Citadel.

- No weapons will be brandished within the Port and Citadel. The only exceptions are for Citadel Guardsmen and Militia.

- Thievery is not tolerated on Dwarven lands.

- Necromancy in any form, whether aiding Necromancers or as a dark magic practitioner, is forbidden from Dwarven lands.

- Deception, Sedition, Sabotage, Cheating, and Trickery will not be tolerated in Citadel military, economic, or political matters.

- No Violent Acts, Invisibility, Illusions, or Offensive Spellcasting within the Port or Citadel.

- Summoning and/or aiding of fiends, devils, or undead is forbidden on Dwarven lands. 

- Followers, worshipers, and those possessing binding pacts with evil or malevolent deities, entities, forces, spirits, or creatures are forbidden from Dwarven lands.


The following is the list of the Banished. The ONLY exceptions are individuals with Council-approved dispensation and Writs of Entry!

Current and Former Servants and Residents of Tarkuul, Goblinoids, Orc-bloods, Fiend-bloods, Giant-bloods, Chromatic-bloods, Kobolds, Duergar, and Drow!
